=====================================================
Complete Workflow: Branch â†’ Edit â†’ Merge Request
Step 1: Clone the Repository (First Time Only)

Open VS Code
Press Cmd + Shift + P
Type: Git: Clone
Paste your repository URL:

   https://gitlab.yourcompany.com/team/lambda-repo.git

Choose where to save (e.g., ~/Documents/Projects)
Enter credentials:

Username: your-gitlab-username
Password: your-personal-access-token (NOT Okta password!)


Click "Open" when prompted


Step 2: Make Sure You Have Latest Code

Look at bottom-left corner of VS Code â†’ you'll see current branch name (probably main)
Press Ctrl + Shift + P (Command Palette)
Type: Git: Pull
Press Enter

This ensures you have the latest code from GitLab.

Step 3: Create a New Branch

Click the branch name in the bottom-left corner (it says main)
A menu opens â†’ Click "Create new branch from..."
Type your branch name:

   upgrade/python-3.13
(or whatever name you want)
4. Press Enter
5. Select "main" as the source branch
6. Press Enter
âœ… You're now on your new branch! You can see it in the bottom-left corner.

Step 4: Make Your Changes (Edit Files)
Now edit the files for your Python 3.13 upgrade:
Option A: Manual Editing

Open files in VS Code (e.g., main.tf, .gitlab-ci.yml)
Make changes:
In Terraform file (main.tf or similar):

hcl   # Change this line:
   runtime = "python3.11"
   
   # To this:
   runtime = "python3.13"
In GitLab CI file (.gitlab-ci.yml):
yaml   # Change this:
   image: python:3.11
   
   # To this:
   image: python:3.13

Save files (Cmd + S)

Option B: Using the Upgrade Script

Open Terminal in VS Code (Ctrl + `)
Run the upgrade script:

bash   # If you have the script
   ./upgrade_to_python313.sh
```

---

### **Step 5: Review Your Changes**

1. Click the **Source Control icon** in left sidebar (or press `Ctrl + Shift + G`)
2. You'll see all changed files listed
3. Click on any file to see what changed (green = added, red = removed)

---

### **Step 6: Commit Your Changes**

1. In the **Source Control panel**
2. Look at the text box that says **"Message"**
3. Type a commit message:
```
   Upgrade Lambda runtime to Python 3.13
```
4. Click the **checkmark (âœ“)** button above the message box

âœ… Your changes are now committed to your branch!

---

### **Step 7: Push Branch to GitLab**

1. Click the **three dots (...)** in Source Control panel
2. Select **"Push"**
3. If it's the first push, you might see a popup â†’ Click **"OK"** or **"Yes"**

Or use this shortcut:
- Bottom-left corner â†’ Click the **â†» sync icon**

âœ… Your branch is now on GitLab!

---

### **Step 8: Create Merge Request (MR)**

Now go to **GitLab in your browser**:

1. Open your browser
2. Go to your GitLab repository
3. You'll see a yellow banner at the top:
```
   You recently pushed to branch: upgrade/python-3.13
   [Create merge request]
```
4. Click **"Create merge request"** button

5. Fill in the Merge Request form:
   - **Title**: `Upgrade Lambda runtime to Python 3.13`
   - **Description**: 
```
     ## Changes
     - Updated Terraform runtime to python3.13
     - Updated GitLab CI image to python:3.13
     
     ## Testing
     - [ ] Tested locally
     - [ ] CI pipeline passed
```
   - **Assignee**: Select your manager or reviewer
   - **Target branch**: Should be `main` (default)

6. Click **"Create merge request"**

âœ… Done! Your manager will get a notification to review.

