What Happens After You Create MR?

Your manager gets notified
They review your code (see what you changed)
They might:

Approve â†’ Merge to main â†’ Your changes go live
Request changes â†’ You make updates â†’ Push again
Ask questions â†’ You discuss in MR comments




If Your Manager Asks for Changes

Stay on the same branch (upgrade/python-3.13)
Make the requested changes in VS Code
Commit again (same process: message â†’ âœ“)
Push again (... â†’ Push)
The Merge Request automatically updates with your new changes!


Common Questions
Q: Can I work on other things while waiting for MR approval?
A: Yes! Just switch back to main branch:

Click branch name (bottom-left)
Select main
Create a new branch for other work

Q: What if I made a mistake?
A: Before pushing:

Just edit the file again and commit
Or undo: Cmd+Shift+P â†’ "Git: Undo Last Commit"

Q: Do I delete the branch after merge?
A: Usually yes, but after it's merged. GitLab will offer to delete it automatically.

Checklist for Your Manager's Requirements

 Created new branch (not working on main)
 Made changes on the branch
 Committed changes
 Pushed branch to GitLab
 Created Merge Request
 Assigned reviewer (your manager)

Follow this process for each Lambda repository you need to upgrade!
